The paper discusses the development of an AI system that can interact with patients and predict diabetes based on non-invasive sensors and deep neural networks. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of deep neural networks also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the analysis of acceptance of young people for AI in healthcare suggests a potential focus on cyberpsychology (cs.CY).
